						<summary>

						<p>ĀTTŪR, ATTUR TALUK, SALEM DISTRICT.</p>						

						<p>Kāyanirmalēśvara temple, west base.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• ••• Year 32.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records an order from Vaṉṉeñjipperumāḷ to be taken note of by the <hi rend="italic">ūravar</hi> of Āṟṟūr, to the effect that 200 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of first grade of wet land in that <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> had been exempted from taxes <hi rend="italic">iṟai-ili</hi> and granted with effect from the date quoted as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḷakkuppuṟam</hi> (a grant for the purpose of maintaining a lamp/lamps) for the Tirumēttaḷi-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār of that <hi rend="italic">ūr.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">ūravar</hi> were to allot and demarcate the land of that extent and plant the boundary stones, have the record inscribed and maintain the lamp.</p>						

						</summary>
